------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3/8/99
    Ordered the EVM bundle.

    Bug when other channel is used.  This is probably due to conflict between
    cleanCut and RMX.

    DPI seems to work on EchoStar, Harmonic Lightway and HITS bitstreams when
    no other channel is used.

    For HITS bitstream, one problem is that the live (80) and ad (400) channels
    seems to have a large difference in the buffer fullness.  As a result, one
    channel is ready, waiting for a long for the other channel to become ready.
    This results in a long PicStat queue.


3/9/99
    Trying to fix the hanging problem.
    The hanging problem is due to PidBuf leaking.

    PidBuf leaking is because the RMX supports only single channel.
    PidBuf of other channel will stay on the queue and lost.
    Solution: Temporarily revert to the original approach for single channel.

    Start compiling in C6x code.

    Created/modified C6x makefiles for each modules.
    Combined cleanCut .c files into single file due to filename too long.


3/10/99
    Trying to reduce the code size to fit program memory (64K)

    After replacing printf() with tgtPrintf() and 
    removing scanf() by hard-coded parameters, the code size reduced from
    120K to 85K.

    Try to use compiler directive
        #pragma CODE_SECTION(func, "my_sect")
    to put non-critical code in external memory.


3/11/99
    Successfully in reducing the code size to fit PMEM by moving non-critical
    code in external RAM.

    Problem: calling a function allocated to a different memory section
             requires the far modifier.

    Migrating to the V2.0 toolset:
        - change the environment C6xDIR to /opt/tools/c6xtools.v20 (in .cshrc)
        - change -Dname to -dname


3/12/99
    Recompiled kernel to use large memory model.
    Reduced .cram size (used for memBlockAlloc()) from 0x5a00 to 0x5600
    memBlockAlloc() allocates memory blocks in on-chip RAM (CRAM) or DRAM.

    Contents that are allocated in CRAM are:
      inBuf[0], outBuf
    Contents that are allocated in DRAM are:
      PidBufs, PicStats, PicHandles, SpliceCmds 

    Successful in compiling and linking the code.

    Start Simulator Debugging phase
    COMMENT OUT memSet() TO SAVE SIMULATOR TIME!  NEED TO TURN BACK ON!!!


